{[show S]Even a passed hand can drive to slam when partner turns up with a powerhouse. Watch how Drury, splinters, and cue-bids assemble the controls one step at a time.
[BID 2C] A third-seat opening shows a real major, and after a pass the opener can be a touch light. Drury exists exactly so a passed hand can sort out how good this 1\S really is. You bid 2\C, Reverse Drury: an artificial good major raise promising about ten support points and at least three trumps. It says "I'm a passed hand, but I have a genuine raise" and asks how much extra opener holds.
[BID 3H] Opener leaps past the minimum 2\D rebid with a splinter, a singleton diamond and a sound 15-plus opening. That bid screams slam interest and pinpoints where the shortness lies. With slam now in the air, you cue-bid 3\H, showing a control in hearts on the way up. Each side starts naming its top cards so they can count toward twelve tricks.
[BID 4D] Opener answers with a surplus, a slam-positive waiting move that confirms there are still extra values to spare. Nobody is backing off the slam hunt. You cue-bid 4\D, a diamond control. With opener short in diamonds and this side holding a control there, the danger suit is covered.
[BID 4N] Opener settles into 4\S, marking spades as trump and inviting the final check before committing to slam. Controls all point the right way, so you bid 4\N, Roman Key Card Blackwood for spades. The keycards are the four aces plus the king of trumps.
[BID 6S] Opener's reply confirms the partnership holds the aces and the trump king it needs, with nothing crucial off the table. Everything checks out, so you bid 6\S. The combined values and located controls make this a sound small slam.
[show NS]South began as a passed hand with about ten points and three-card spade support, exactly the holding Drury was built to show. The 2\C raise, the heart and diamond cue-bids, and the keycard answer painted that hand precisely, and opposite partner's powerful opening the controls were all present. Twelve tricks roll in for 6\S making six.}
